  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Opening:</strong> Use <code>dialog.showModal()</code> for modal behavior with backdrop</li>
        <li><strong>Closing:</strong> Use <code>dialog.close()</code> or let users press Escape</li>
        <li><strong>Return value:</strong> Use <code>method="dialog"</code> on forms to get the submit button's value</li>
        <li><strong>Focus:</strong> First focusable element receives focus when opened</li>
        <li><strong>Click outside:</strong> Add click listener on dialog to close when clicking backdrop</li>
        <li><strong>Scrolling:</strong> For long content, add a scrollable class to the body section</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>

